1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE
RESOLUTION 1049 By: Newton
4
5
6
7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Resolution designating the month of May as Asthma
and Allergy Awareness Month.
9
10
11
12 WHEREAS, about 4,750,000 children in the United States have been
13 diagnosed with asthma; and
14 WHEREAS, nearly 28 million people in the United States have
15 asthma; and
16 WHEREAS, over 437,000 adults and children in Oklahoma suffer
17 from asthma; and
18 WHEREAS, asthma is one of the most common noncommunicable
19 diseases among children; and
20 WHEREAS, 1 million individuals per year visit emergency
21 departments because of asthma's effects; and
22 WHEREAS, asthma is a leading cause of hospitalizations and
23 school absences due to a chronic disease among children; and
24
Req. No. 17327 Page 1

1 WHEREAS, the total economic impact of asthma in the United
2 States was $81,900,000,000 per year from 2008 to 2013, which is
3 approximately $115,000,000,000 when adjusted for inflation; and
4 WHEREAS, Black, Hispanic, and Indigenous individuals in the
5 United States face the highest burden of asthma; and
6 WHEREAS, asthma is a manageable disease that claimed lives of
7 over 3,100 people in the United States in 2023, including 50 people
8 in Oklahoma; and
9 WHEREAS, people with asthma and food allergies need access to
10 affordable health insurance and to the medications and devices they
11 need at affordable prices; and
12 WHEREAS, 21,800,000 people in the United States have food
13 allergies, including about 3,900,000 children; and
14 WHEREAS, food allergy has increased among United States children
15 over the past 20 years, with the greatest increase in Black
16 children; and
17 WHEREAS, children with food allergies are two to four times more
18 likely to have asthma or other allergic diseases; and
19 WHEREAS, May is an appropriate month to designate as "Asthma and
20 Allergy Awareness Month".
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
22 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGILSATURE:
23
24
Req. No. 17327 Page 2

1 THAT the members of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, do
2 hereby proclaim the month of May 2026 as Asthma and Allergy
3 Awareness Month.
4 THAT the members call upon the people of the State of Oklahoma
5 to observe such month with appropriate ceremonies and activities.
